column4: All the serious problems are being ignored, while all the newbies are getting help. I ask questions whose answers aren't documented elsewhere. I hate to beg for attention, but this is getting ridiculous. :\
I have two. Which would you rather cover? Nautilus being retarded, or Java not working after Sun JRE was installed from the multiverse repository?
First Nautilus is always buggy we can work on that. , Java  runtime?  is yes should be installed directly from sun.
what are the issues you are having with nautilus

Well, it was running quite happily for a couple weeks, now. I played with GTK-Gnutella and mplayer off and on during this time. Suddenly it decided to have a seizure, and after I restarted it for the fifth time, it continues to give nothing but a blank window that acts like it's lagging to hell. This, of course, means that I have no desktop as well.
Have you cleared your Nautlius Temp files yet?
Oh.. No, I haven't. Where are they stored? Is there a command or do I have to wipe the directory with rm -r >
Well, gee, you could have just told me they were in .nautilus. I know my way around. Thanks for the help, though. :)
you said it was multipul choice  i didn't want you confused :d
Eh... That didn't do it, it seems.
Yes. K3B says the operation isn't permitted, though.
Oh. Now I see what you meant. Lemme check that path.
